1. Declarative

Meaning:
In React, you tell React what the UI should look like for a given data state. React automatically updates the screen when data changes.

Example
function Welcome() {
  return <h1>Hello Student</h1>;
}

Instead of manually changing HTML elements, React handles updates automatically.

Advantage
Easy to write
Easy to understand
Easy to debug






2. Component-Based

Meaning:
React applications are built using small reusable pieces called components.

Example
function Header() {
  return <h1>My Website</h1>;
}

function Footer() {
  return <p>Copyright 2026</p>;
}

Here:

Header = Component
Footer = Component

We combine components to build a complete application.

Advantage
Reusable code
Easy maintenance
Better organization



